---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About CareCost Intelligence | Independent Senior Care Planning" description="Learn what CareCost Intelligence does, who the site is built for, how our planning model works, and why families use it to compare senior care costs before collecting final quotes.">
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="pill">Independent planning platform</span>
      <h1>About CareCost Intelligence</h1>
      <p class="note">Updated: Mar 2026. CareCost Intelligence helps families compare senior care cost scenarios before they commit to provider tours, care transitions, or long-term budgets.</p>
      <div class="tag">Last updated: Mar 2026</div>
      <div class="editorial-meta">Reviewed by CareCost Intelligence Editorial Team</div>
      <div class="author-box">
        <div class="author-title">Site overview</div>
        <div class="author-meta">
          <div>
            <strong>CareCost Intelligence Editorial Team</strong>
            <p class="note">For full transparency, review our <a href="/editorial-policy/">Editorial Policy</a>, <a href="/methodology/">Methodology</a>, and <a href="/updates/">Updates &amp; Corrections</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chip-grid" style="margin-top: 12px;">
        <a class="chip" href="#mission">Mission</a>
        <a class="chip" href="#who-we-serve">Who we serve</a>
        <a class="chip" href="#what-we-publish">What we publish</a>
        <a class="chip" href="#how-we-work">How we work</a>
        <a class="chip" href="#what-we-do-not-do">What we do not do</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="mission">
    <div class="container grid-2">
      <div class="card">
        <h2>Our mission</h2>
        <p>We help families make clearer, calmer senior care decisions by turning confusing cost questions into usable planning ranges, checklists, and comparison workflows.</p>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li>Make cost planning easier to understand.</li>
          <li>Reduce surprises before provider tours.</li>
          <li>Encourage quote validation instead of guesswork.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h2>Why this site exists</h2>
        <p>Many families receive incomplete quotes, inconsistent care tier descriptions, and little guidance on how to compare options fairly. This site was built to close that gap.</p>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li>Ranges instead of false precision.</li>
          <li>Tool-first workflows instead of generic content.</li>
          <li>Trust and transparency before monetization.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="who-we-serve">
    <div class="container grid-3">
      <div class="card feature">
        <h3>Families comparing options</h3>
        <p>Use the estimator and guides to compare assisted living, memory care, home care, and nursing home scenarios.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card feature">
        <h3>Caregivers planning transitions</h3>
        <p>Stress-test a higher care tier before a move, reassessment, or change in living situation.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card feature">
        <h3>Budget-minded decision makers</h3>
        <p>Use planning ranges, budget-gap signals, and validation checklists before committing to quotes.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="what-we-publish">
    <div class="container card">
      <h2>What we publish</h2>
      <div class="grid-2">
        <div>
          <h3>Estimator</h3>
          <ul class="checklist">
            <li>Low, median, and high planning ranges.</li>
            <li>Budget-gap and comparison workflows.</li>
            <li>Care-fit and affordability framing.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Guidance</h3>
          <ul class="checklist">
            <li>State guides for local validation context.</li>
            <li>Care-type comparisons and planning guides.</li>
            <li>Checklists for quote collection and provider review.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="controls" style="margin-top: 14px;">
        <a class="btn" href="/estimator/">Use the estimator</a>
        <a class="btn secondary" href="/guides/">Browse guides</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="how-we-work">
    <div class="container grid-2">
      <div class="card">
        <h2>How we work</h2>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li>We explain assumptions openly in our <a href="/methodology/">Methodology</a>.</li>
          <li>We document public references in <a href="/data-sources/">Data Sources</a>.</li>
          <li>We log meaningful changes on <a href="/updates/">Updates &amp; Corrections</a>.</li>
          <li>We separate planning content from promotional claims.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h2>How to contact us</h2>
        <p>If you find an outdated source, a confusing section, or a broken calculation flow, contact us and include the page URL plus the issue you found.</p>
        <ul class="checklist">
          <li>Editorial feedback and corrections.</li>
          <li>Methodology questions.</li>
          <li>Technical estimator issues.</li>
          <li>Licensing or partnership requests.</li>
        </ul>
        <a class="tag" href="/contact/">Contact CareCost Intelligence</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="what-we-do-not-do">
    <div class="container card">
      <h2>What we do not do</h2>
      <div class="grid-3">
        <div class="feature">
          <strong>No provider referrals</strong>
          <p class="note">We do not match families to specific facilities or agencies.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <strong>No medical or financial advice</strong>
          <p class="note">The site supports planning and comparison, not professional advice or diagnosis.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="feature">
          <strong>No guaranteed pricing</strong>
          <p class="note">Provider quotes, care tier schedules, and move-in fees must be verified locally.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
